    "plan_content": "Here's my implementation plan for `uv cache stats`:\n\n---\n\n## What I found\n\nThe codebase already has `uv cache size` (behind `PreviewFeature::CacheSize`) which uses `diskus::DiskUsage` to measure the whole cache root in one shot. The `CacheBucket` enum defines 11 buckets (Wheels, SourceDistributions, Simple, FlatIndex, Git, Interpreter, Archive, Builds, Environments, Python, Binaries), each mapping to a versioned subdirectory. `Cache::bucket(CacheBucket)` is already `pub` and returns the `PathBuf` for any bucket — no changes to `uv-cache` are needed.\n\n---\n\n## Plan summary (8 touch-points, 2 new files)\n\n**New file: `crates/uv/src/commands/cache_stats.rs`**\n- Defines a constant `ALL_BUCKETS` slice (includes `Python`, which `CacheBucket::iter()` intentionally omits for clean/prune)\n- Loops over each bucket, calls `DiskUsage::new(vec![path]).count_ignoring_errors()` (skipping non-existent paths as `0`)\n- Prints one aligned line per bucket using `bucket` `Display` (→ `\"wheels-v6:\"` etc.)\n- Prints `Total:` at the end\n- Same `--human` / `human_readable_bytes()` / `warn_user!` preview-gate pattern as `cache_size.rs`\n\n**`crates/uv-preview/src/lib.rs`** — add `CacheStats = 1 << 28` variant + `\"cache-stats\"` string\n\n**`crates/uv-cli/src/lib.rs`** — add `Stats(StatsArgs)` to `CacheCommand`, add `StatsArgs { human: bool }` (identical shape to `SizeArgs`)\n\n**`crates/uv/src/commands/mod.rs`** — `mod cache_stats;` + re-export\n\n**`crates/uv/src/lib.rs`** — dispatch `CacheCommand::Stats(args)` → `commands::cache_stats(&cache, args.human, printer, globals.preview)`\n\n**`crates/uv-test/src/lib.rs`** — add `fn cache_stats()` command helper + `fn with_filtered_cache_stats()` snapshot filter\n\n**`crates/uv/tests/it/main.rs`** — add `mod cache_stats;` under the same `#[cfg(all(feature = \"test-python\", feature = \"test-pypi\"))]` gate\n\n**New file: `crates/uv/tests/it/cache_stats.rs`** — 3 integration tests: empty cache, raw bytes with packages, human-readable with packages",
